gomodel:SYNGO_5336  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" , "Rationale: Figure 1, Table 1: immunogold EM localization of GABA-A ρ3 subunit (GABRR3) in wildtype mouse neostriatum showed approximately half of the staining at the postsynaptic membrane (i.e. the remainder was extrasynaptic).. Experimental description: Mice were used for all experiments. Result section, discussing EM data from Figure 3; \"Furthermore, the α-synuclein signal was used to distinguish presynaptic regions. As expected, the labels (nanogold particles with asterisks) for all five GABA-A tonic subunits were found at extrasynaptic (ES) and perisynaptic (PS) sites preferentially, with scarcely signal in the synaptic clefts (S), in control mice at 6 months of age.\"\n\nantibody:\nRabbit Anti GABA-A rho3, Santa Cruz, sc28793" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5336" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

